-- South Africa Richards Bay Coal Decreases Most in Five Months
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-12-17T11:44:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-17/south-africa-richards-bay-coal-decreases-most-in-five-months.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
Richards Bay, the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, declined most in five months.  Coal for  immediate delivery  dropped $3.11, or 3.5 percent,
to $86.62 a metric ton in the week to Dec. 14, the biggest drop
since July 13, according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg.  The fuel is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which excludes
delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
